# Our findings in the process

During the process of teaching the TCP, we achieved some findings and best practice routines.

## AS Language vs Automatic teaching

The different methods has their pros and cons in different situations. It is now our understanding that the **AS language method** is the most fool proff of the ladder. 

The **Automatic method** primarily has it use cases when the tool is in alignment or a 90 degree angle from the flange. 

When more angles are at hand, it was difficult to get satisfactory results.

We used the **Automatic method** for the vacuum suction cup with acceptable results. We recon it would be acceptable for welding heads or similar tools as well.

